<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1909-03-10T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1909-03-10T00:00:00-05:00" n="368" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d368">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Dawson</persName> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Bogota</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1909-03-10"><hi rend="italic">March 10,
                                1909</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Student demonstrations against the treaties yesterday. The President of
                            Colombia has issued a decree to-day confiding maintenance order to
                            minister of war. Motion to postpone consideration of the treaties has
                            been defeated, 40 to 6.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Dawson.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>